  "text": "In general, girls were found to have a lower HRQOL in comparison with boys (24) . In the present study, this was supported in only two dimensions: girls perception of their own body appearance was more negatively, and they were more concerned about their looks as well as their clothes (selfperception). In addition, they reported a lower physical wellbeing than boys. This result was consistent with a previous study [CITATION_1] .",
